<dl id="n22044e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22044e">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22044e"> 44(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> put out fire / curfew</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The good man was again informed that the cur&eacute; used to come and put out the fire at his house every night,(*) as he did before he was forbidden. The foolish husband, hearing that, was much astonished and also angry, and to remedy this state of affairs, thought of the means which I will relate. <font color="green">[(*) That is to say came at curfew time.]</font> <small> Robert B. Douglas, trans., <a name="RBDM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBDM"><cite title="source">ONE HUNDRED MERRIE AND DELIGHTSOME STORIES</cite></a> (1923) Story 73</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
